            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "lua don't seem provide a good \"maxint\", maybe it's because all lua number is float... So it's fun that `math.huge` seems overflow:\n\n```\n$ echo 'vim.wait(math.huge)' | nvim -l -\nE5113: Lua chunk: [string \"vim.wait(math.huge)...\"]:1: timeout must be >= 0\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'wait'\n        [string \"vim.wait(math.huge)...\"]:1: in main chunk\n```\n\nThis work: `echo 'vim.wait(vim._maxint)' | nvim -l -`\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7838c242e96c4f6c6432a997234bb2dbdbfea658/runtime/lua/vim/shared.lua#L1617-L1618\n\nIt's about 24 days. Ok I never make a instance live longer than that period.\n",
