            "body": "> > `math.huge` seems overflow:\n> \n> doesn't happen for me, seems like a bug. are you on a 32-bit system? are you using luajit or puc lua ? check `:version`.\n\nIt happens for me (`:lua vim.wait(math.huge)`):\n```\nE5108: Lua: [string \":lua\"]:1: timeout must be >= 0\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'wait'\n\t[string \":lua\"]:1: in main chunk\n```\n\nHere's `:version`. I'm on a 64-bit system.\n\n```\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev+1775-62dd74d47\nBuild type: RelWithDebInfo\nLuaJIT 2.1.1761727121\n```\n\nPersonally, I'm not in favor of making `vim.wait(-1)` be special-cased (code that does `vim.wait(v1 - v2)` shouldn't have the chance to hang forever, only error), but using `vim.wait(math.huge)` should probably be fixed.",
